p.text: Stock prediction system based on financial news
2 Billion shares are traded on NASDAQ daily...
Over 100K Companies are publically traded all over the world...
The Global Stock market size is close to US $55 trillion
Volkswagen lost almost a quarter of its market value after news was out about cheating on U.S. air pollution tests for years
It plunged as much as 23 percent to 125.40 euros in Frankfurt, wiping out about 15.6 billion euros ($17.6 billion) in market value
The stock closed at 132.2 euros, its lowest in more than three years
After the news of iphone 6 bending problem was out Apple stock suffered a loss of 23% in stock prices.
A news of an oil spill caused BP's corporate shares fall from $60 to $27 in one month, wiping out $100 billion in shareholder value
The Dow reacted favorably to the news,
when the rate increase was announced by Federal Reserve, the industrial average was steadily risen and closed up 1.28%.
Understand relationship and predict the movement of stock prices in the market based on financial news
Create a portfolio based on user specified criteria for recommending best investment options to users
Initially we would create different models for classification (up, down, stable)
Choose the best model for stock price prediction using regression
Capital Asset pricing model introduced by Jack Treynor in 1962
Stock prices for the past five years of top 100 most traded companies registered on NASDAQ (Yahoo Finance API)
Written a script which automates the downloading process by specifying dates and providing list of companies
Financial news data of past five years using RSS feeds of various news platforms. various (NYTimes, Wall Street Journal etc) is available through google news api.
We automate the collection step using a shell script where query api and store the xml data.
Data is collected as xml, but contains html css stype information.
Need to be cleaned before use.
